 ‚çù? Ok, we've got a problem here. If the user executes an event-handler that contains a branch, then it jumps out of ‚àÜWI without ever having
 ‚çù? a chance to clean up (especially the quad-vars). The only thing I can think of so far is cutting off the expression at the point of the
 ‚çù? branch and putting it into a global for ‚àÜWI to perform the last thing before it returns (probably from a Wait).
 ‚çù? Don't do this for quoted strings unless they're being ‚çé'd, which makes it an even a bigger mess.
 ‚çù? Got any better ideas?

